ver that uses an OpenGL version higher than stated in the GPU spec (note 500 series NVidia cards only technically go to 4.1 but modern 500 series driver uses 4.4)  will possibly have issues.tl;dr this game used to run well and it doesn't universally run well anymore, use the original on GoG or if you have the disks, the only reason to buy a beamdog update is for IceWind Dale because the old infinite engine ran on IPX for multiplayer which is no longer supported outside of WindowsXP and is only workable for local area networking.The March 31 update for this is UNSIGHTLY, UGLY, and ultimately destroys any semblance of authenticity to the aesthetics of the original and should not be bought. as of now i will be using the original from GoG or my CDs, THIS IS AN AFFRONT TO THE USERS AND SHOULD NEVER HAVE BEEN DONE!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!"
