76561198008048666,Recommended,257350,28075682,"Posted: 29 November, 2016",all,Tpalmi,"This is simply one of the greatest RPGs of all time. the characters are absolutely fantastic in every way, from comical to depressing. The storylines run the gauntlet from short and surprising to sweeping epics of betrayal. The world is so much deeper and richer than almost anything else that has been released since. You will find yourself sent on small errand quests that uncover plot twist after plot twist and now you're fighting a subterranean old god under the sewers. You will be infiltrating thieves guilds and trudging through the underdark.It is also one of the least linear gaming experiences you will ever have. At times you're only given long term goals like ""you need to pay X amount to gain the help of Y group, here you are in this city, go find a way to make tons of money""Yes, the rule set can be a little daunting in the beginning as it is based on old 2nd edition d&d, which is widely known to be highly unintuitive and even, at times, contradictory. Fortunately it really only takes a few minutes to learn the basics in the form of, lower armor class is harder to hit, higher saving throws helps you avoid things, do more damage to kill things faster.Honestly just give it a chance, explore a little bit and you're almost guaranteed to be hooked."
